== 政治 ==
{{Main|保加利亞政治}}
保加利亞是[[议会共和制|议会共和制]]國家，總理是政府首腦。虽然總統的權力有限，但可以行使覆議權让[[议会|议会]]再次讨论。议会则可通过多数决议议会让该被驳回的法律生效。由240名代表組成的[[一院制|一院制]]國民議會通過直接普選選出，任期四年，拥有立法、批准政府开支预算、计划总统选举、选举或撤除总理、宣战、决定在国外驻军和批准外交协议的权力。<ref name="DD-Navi">{{cite web|url=http://direct-democracy-navigator.org/countries/bulgaria/legal_designs|title=Overview of direct democratic instruments in Bulgaria|publisher=Navigator to Direct Democracy|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140116183501/http://direct-democracy-navigator.org/countries/bulgaria/legal_designs|archive-date=2014-01-16|access-date=2018-07-25}}</ref>

總體而言，保加利亞顯示出政府不穩定的模式<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSFit981123|title=Fitch: Early Bulgaria Elections Would Create Fiscal Uncertainty|work=Reuters|date=2016-11-23|access-date=2018-07-09|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512222756/https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSFit981123}}</ref>。2009年至2021年期間，博伊科·鮑里索夫擔任了三屆總理<ref name="WP1">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2017/04/25/bulgarias-government-will-include-nationalist-parties-on-the-far-right-heres-why-and-what-this-means/|title=Bulgaria's government will include far-right nationalist parties for the first time|newspaper=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|first=Nina|last=Barzachka|date=2017-04-25|access-date=2018-07-09|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512222921/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/monkey-cage/wp/2017/04/25/bulgarias-government-will-include-nationalist-parties-on-the-far-right-heres-why-and-what-this-means/}}</ref>，當時他的中右翼親歐盟黨GERB贏得了大選，並在國民議會中以117個席位的少數政府身份執政<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-04-06/bulgarian-cabinet-faces-no-confidence-vote-over-atomic-plant |title=Bulgarian Cabinet Faces No-Confidence Vote Over Atomic Plant |magazine=[[Bloomberg_Businessweek|Bloomberg Businessweek]] |date=2012-04-06 |access-date=2012-06-01 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726205035/http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-04-06/bulgarian-cabinet-faces-no-confidence-vote-over-atomic-plant |archive-date=2013-07-26 }}</ref>。他的第一屆政府於2013年2月20日在全國范圍內因公用事業成本高、生活水平低、腐敗和民主制度的失敗而引發抗議後辭職<ref>{{cite news |title=Bulgarian government resigns amid growing protests |url=https://news.yahoo.com/bulgaria-government-resigns-national-protests-073220738.html?.b=index&.cf3=World+News&.cf4=1&.cf5=Reuters&.cf6=/ |work=Yahoo! News|first=Sam|last=Cage|access-date=2013-02-20 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130308142025/http://news.yahoo.com/bulgaria-government-resigns-national-protests-073220738.html?.b=index&.cf3=World+News&.cf4=1&.cf5=Reuters&.cf6=%2F |archive-date= 2013-03-08 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2013/02/201322163943882279.html|title=Protests in Bulgaria and the new practice of democracy|publisher=Al Jazeera|first=Mariya|last=Petkova|date=2013-02-21|access-date=2013-03-07|archive-date=2013-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130622043541/http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/2013/02/201322163943882279.html}}</ref>。隨後在5月舉行的提前選舉導致GERB以微弱優勢獲勝<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bulgaria-election-idUSBRE94A09920130512|title=Rightist GERB holds lead in Bulgaria's election|work=Reuters|first=Tsvetelia|last=Tsolova|date=2013-05-12|access-date=2013-05-15|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924181140/http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/05/12/us-bulgaria-election-idUSBRE94A09920130512|url-status=live}}</ref>，但在鮑里索夫未能獲得議會支持後，保加利亞社會黨最終組建了由帕門·奧列沙斯基領導的政府<ref name="form">{{cite web|url=http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=150686|title=PM Hopeful: New Bulgarian Cabinet Will Be 'Expert, Pragmatic'|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|date=2013-05-25|access-date=2014-03-12|archive-date=2014-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140313002312/http://www.novinite.com/view_news.php?id=150686}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Neil|last=Buckley|title=Bulgaria parliament votes for a 'Mario Monti' to lead government|url=https://www.ft.com/content/fc0873ba-c7b2-11e2-9c52-00144feab7de|newspaper=The Financial Times|date=2013-05-29|access-date=2018-07-28|archive-date=2022-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425154320/https://www.ft.com/content/fc0873ba-c7b2-11e2-9c52-00144feab7de}}</ref>。在持續的大規模抗議活動中，奧列沙斯基政府於2014年7月辭職<ref>{{cite web|title=Bulgarians protest government of 'oligarchs'|url=https://www.dw.com/en/bulgarians-protest-government-of-oligarchs/a-16909751|publisher=Deutsche Welle|first=Bistra|last=Seiler|date=2013-06-26|access-date=2018-07-28|archive-date=2015-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610233330/http://www.dw.de/bulgarians-protest-government-of-oligarchs/a-16909751}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/162221/Timeline+of+Oresharski%27s+Cabinet%3A+A+Government+in+Constant+Jeopardy|title=Timeline of Oresharski's Cabinet: A Government in Constant Jeopardy|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|date=2014-07-24|access-date=2014-07-29|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512222829/https://www.novinite.com/articles/162221/Timeline+of+Oresharski%27s+Cabinet%3A+A+Government+in+Constant+Jeopardy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/162217/Bulgaria%27s+PM+Plamen+Oresharski+Resigns%7Ctitle=Bulgaria's%20PM%20Plamen%20Oresharski%20Resigns|title=Bulgaria's Plamen Oresharski resigns|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|date=2014-07-23|access-date=2014-07-25|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512222814/https://www.novinite.com/articles/162217/Bulgaria%27s+PM+Plamen+Oresharski+Resigns%7Ctitle=Bulgaria%27s%20PM%20Plamen%20Oresharski%20Resigns}}</ref>。看守政府接管並召集了2014年10月的選舉<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.novinite.com/articles/162494/Bulgaria's+President+Names+Georgi+Bliznashki+as+Prime+Minister|title=Bulgaria's President Names Georgi Bliznashki as Prime Minister|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|date=2014-08-05|access-date=2016-04-07|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512222819/https://www.novinite.com/articles/162494/Bulgaria%27s+President+Names+Georgi+Bliznashki+as+Prime+Minister}}</ref><ref name="Sofia News Agency">{{cite web|url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/162542/Bulgaria%27s+42nd+Parliament+Dissolved%2C+Elections+on+October+5|title=Bulgaria's 42nd Parliament Dissolved, Elections on October 5|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|date=2014-08-06|access-date=2014-08-09|archive-date=2022-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220510100917/https://www.novinite.com/articles/162542/Bulgaria%27s+42nd+Parliament+Dissolved%2C+Elections+on+October+5}}</ref>，這導致了GERB的第三次勝利，但共有八個政黨進入議會<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.novinite.com/articles/163898/Bulgaria%27s+Grand+Parliament+Chessboard+Might+Be+Both+Ailment+and+Cure|title=Bulgaria's Grand Parliament Chessboard Might Be Both Ailment and Cure|publisher=[[Novinite|Novinite]]|first=Angel|last=Petrov|date=2014-10-06|access-date=2014-10-07|archive-date=2020-09-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200907081534/https://www.novinite.com/articles/163898/Bulgaria%27s+Grand+Parliament+Chessboard+Might+Be+Both+Ailment+and+Cure}}</ref>。鮑里索夫與幾個右翼政黨組成聯盟<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bulgaria-government-idUSKBN0IQ1ID20141106|title=Bulgaria's Borisov plasters together coalition government|work=Reuters|first=Tsvetelia|last=Tsolova|date=2014-11-06|access-date=2018-07-28|archive-date=2022-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220419163046/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-bulgaria-government-idUSKBN0IQ1ID20141106}}</ref>，但在其政黨支持的候選人未能贏得2016年總統大選後再次辭職。[[保加利亞歐洲發展公民黨|GERB]]再次贏得了2017年3月的提前選舉，但在議會中擁有95個席位<ref>Todorov, Svetoslav (10 July 2020). [https://balkaninsight.com/2020/07/10/fresh-protest-wave-gains-momentum-in-bulgaria/ "Fresh Protest Wave Gains Momentum in Bulgaria."] {{Wayback|url=https://balkaninsight.com/2020/07/10/fresh-protest-wave-gains-momentum-in-bulgaria/ |date=20220416233504 }} ''BalkanInsight.com''. Retrieved 20 July 2021.</ref><ref>[https://www.dw.com/en/bulgaria-anti-government-protests-continue-for-a-ninth-day/a-54224137 "Bulgaria: Anti-Government Protests Continue for a Ninth Day"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.dw.com/en/bulgaria-anti-government-protests-continue-for-a-ninth-day/a-54224137 |date=20220416233508 }} (18 July 2020). ''DW.com''. Retrieved 20 July 2021.</ref>。他們與擁有27個席位的極右翼聯合愛國者聯盟結成了聯盟<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/bulgaria-election-pm-borissovs-party-wins-but-falls-short-of-majority/a-57102610|title=Bulgaria election: PM Borissov's party wins but falls short of majority | DW | 05.04.2021|website=[[Deutsche_Welle|Deutsche Welle]]|access-date=2022-01-21|archive-date=2022-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220427234315/https://www.dw.com/en/bulgaria-election-pm-borissovs-party-wins-but-falls-short-of-majority/a-57102610}}</ref>。鮑里索夫的上一屆內閣見證了新聞自由的急劇下降，以及一些腐敗事件的揭露，引發了2020年的又一波大規模抗議活動<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/bulgaria-faces-fresh-elections-socialists-refuse-form-government-2021-05-01/| title = Reuters| access-date = 2022-01-21| archive-date = 2021-05-08| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210508182040/https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/bulgaria-faces-fresh-elections-socialists-refuse-form-government-2021-05-01/}}</ref>。GERB在2021年4月的常規選舉中首先出現，但其結果是迄今為止最弱的。所有其他黨派都拒絕組建政府，在短暫的僵局之後，又要求在2021年7月舉行另一次選舉，屆時斯特凡·亞內夫將擔任看守內閣的臨時總理<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/bulgarias-caretaker-prime-minister-says-priority-is-rule-law-2021-05-12/| title = Reuters| access-date = 2022-01-21| archive-date = 2022-04-25| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220425105714/https://www.reuters.com/world/europe/bulgarias-caretaker-prime-minister-says-priority-is-rule-law-2021-05-12/}}</ref>。在2021年7月的提前選舉中，反精英政黨ITN以24.08%的得票率位居第一，前總理博伊科·鮑里索夫領導的GERB聯盟以23.51%的得票率位居第二<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/bulgaria-elections-borisov-gerb-trifonov/31357002.html |title=Final Results In Bulgarian Vote Confirm Win For Anti-Elite Party |work=Radio Free Europe |date=2021-07-13 |access-date=2021-08-23 |url-status=live |archive-date=2021-07-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210713230750/https://www.rferl.org/a/bulgaria-elections-borisov-gerb-trifonov/31357002.html }}</ref>。

自由之家報告稱，2009 年後民主治理持續惡化，理由是媒體獨立性下降、改革停滯不前、最高層濫用職權以及地方政府對中央政府的依賴增加<ref name="FH">{{cite web|url=https://freedomhouse.org/report/nations-transit/2018/bulgaria|title=Bulgaria Country Profile|publisher=Freedom House|first=Emilia|last=Zankina|access-date=2018-07-24|archive-date=2018-07-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724154012/https://freedomhouse.org/report/nations-transit/2018/bulgaria}}</ref>。保加利亞仍被列為“自由”，其政治制度被定為半民主國家，儘管分數不斷下降，民主指數將其定義為“有缺陷的民主”<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eiu.com/public/topical_report.aspx?campaignid=DemocracyIndex2017|title=Democracy Index 2017: Free speech under attack|publisher=The Economist Intelligence Unit|access-date=2018-07-24|archive-date=2018-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180131181010/https://www.eiu.com/public/topical_report.aspx?campaignid=DemocracyIndex2017}}</ref>。

== 行政区划 ==
{{保加利亚地图|float=right}}
{{main|保加利亚行政区划|l1=}}
保加利亞是一個單一制國家<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ccre.org/en/membres/Bulgarie.htm |title=Local Structures in Bulgaria |publisher=Council of European Municipalities and Regions |access-date=2012-04-11 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120604090547/http://www.ccre.org/en/membres/Bulgarie.htm |archive-date=2012-06-04 }}</ref>。自1880年代以來，行政區劃的數量從7個變化到26個<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mrrb.government.bg/index.php?controller=articles&id=4216 |script-title=bg:Историческо развитие на административно–териториалното устройство на Република България|trans-title=Historical development of the administrative and territorial division of the Republic of Bulgaria|publisher=Ministry of Regional Development|language=bg|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140202100126/http://www.mrrb.government.bg/index.php?controller=articles&id=4216|archive-date=2014-02-02|access-date=2018-07-28}}</ref>。1987年至1999年間，行政結構由九個省組成。在經濟體制下放的同時，採用了新的行政結構。它包括27個省和一個首都特區。所有地區的名字都取自各自的首府。各省細分為265個市<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mrrb.government.bg/index.php?lang=bg&do=atums&type=71&id=13|title=Областите в България. Портрети|trans-title=The oblasts in Bulgaria. Portraits|publisher=Ministry of Regional Development|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120619040835/http://www.mrrb.government.bg/index.php?lang=bg&do=atums&type=71&id=13|archive-date=2012-06-19|access-date=2018-07-28}}</ref>。

== 地理 ==
{{main|保加利亞地理}}
保加利亞位於歐洲東南部、巴爾幹半島東部。北與羅馬尼亞接壤，西與塞爾維亞和北馬其頓、希臘接壤，南臨土耳其，東臨黑海。[[多瑙河|多瑙河]]是保加利亚与罗马尼亚的界河。其領土面積為110,994平方公里，與五個鄰國的陸地邊界總長1,808公里，海岸線長354公里。巴爾干山脈從西向東橫貫該國中部，将保加利亚分为北部的多瑙河平原和南部的色雷斯低地，西南部是[[罗多彼山脉|罗多彼山脉]]，其最高峰[[穆萨拉峰|穆萨拉峰]]高2925米，是保加利亚和巴尔干半岛的最高点。平原約佔領土的三分之一，而高原和丘陵則佔41%。<ref name="CIA World Factbook">{{cite web|url=https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/bulgaria/|title=Bulgaria|website=[[The_World_Factbook|The World Factbook]]|publisher=[[Central_Intelligence_Agency|Central Intelligence Agency]]|access-date=2011-12-04|archive-date=2021-01-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210109224217/https://www.cia.gov/the-world-factbook/countries/bulgaria/}}</ref>

保加利亞地處地中海、大洋和大陸氣團的交匯點，加上山脈的屏障效應，氣候多變。與巴爾干山脈以南的地區相比，保加利亞北部平均氣溫低1°C，降水量多200毫米。不同地區的溫度幅度差異很大。記錄的最低溫度為-38.3°C，而最高溫度為45.2°C。年平均降水量約為630毫米，在山區超過2,500毫米。大陸氣團在冬季帶來大量降雪。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://unfccc.int/resource/docs/natc/bulnc2.pdf|title=Bulgaria Second National Communication|publisher=[[United_Nations_Framework_Convention_on_Climate_Change|United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change]]|access-date=2018-10-09|archive-date=2022-04-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220425123303/https://unfccc.int/resource/docs/natc/bulnc2.pdf}}</ref>

保加利亞超過35%的土地面積被森林覆蓋<ref>{{cite web |url=http://data.un.org/en/iso/bg.html |title=Bulgaria – Environmental Summary, UNData, United Nations |publisher=United Nations |access-date=2011-12-20 |archive-date=2021-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211222045515/http://data.un.org/en/iso/bg.html }}</ref>。氣候、水文、地質和地形條件的相互作用產生了相對廣泛的植物和動物物種<ref name="biodiversity">{{cite web|url=http://www.flora.biodiversity.bg/bg_flora_fr.htm|title=Характеристика на флората и растителността на България|publisher=Bulgarian-Swiss Program For Biodiversity|access-date=2013-03-21|archive-date=2013-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130427002409/http://www.flora.biodiversity.bg/bg_flora_fr.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref>。保加利亞是歐洲生物多樣性最豐富的國家之一<ref name="diversity of flora and fauna">{{cite web|url=http://unesco-bg.org/file_store/2._bogatstvobr_25.1.10.pdf|script-title=bg:Видово разнообразие на България|trans-title=Species biodiversity in Bulgaria|publisher=UNESCO report|language=bg|date=2013|access-date=2018-07-30|archive-date=2015-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714213353/http://unesco-bg.org/file_store/2._bogatstvobr_25.1.10.pdf}}</ref>，在3個國家公園、11個自然公園、10個生物圈保護區和565個保護區中得到保護<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gorabg-magazine.info/bg/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14&showall=1|title=Бъдещето на природните паркове в България и техните администрации|trans-title=The future of Bulgaria's natural parks and their administrations|publisher=Gora Magazine|first=Toma|last=Belev|date=June 2010|access-date=2011-12-20|archive-date=2011-11-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111102101145/http://www.gorabg-magazine.info/bg/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=14&showall=1}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/environment/ecological-sciences/biosphere-reserves/europe-north-america/|title=Europe & North America: 297 biosphere reserves in 36 countries|publisher=[[UNESCO|UNESCO]]|access-date=2016-04-04|archive-date=2015-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150805094626/http://www.unesco.org/new/en/natural-sciences/environment/ecological-sciences/biosphere-reserves/europe-north-america}}</ref>。歐洲233種哺乳動物中有93種在保加利亞發現，還有49%的蝴蝶和30%的維管植物物種<ref name="IUCN">{{cite web|url=https://cmsdata.iucn.org/downloads/bulgaria_s_biodiversity_at_risk_fact_sheet_may_2013.pdf|title=Bulgaria's biodiversity at risk|publisher=[[IUCN_Red_List|IUCN Red List]]|date=2013|access-date=2018-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150504023321/https://cmsdata.iucn.org/downloads/bulgaria_s_biodiversity_at_risk_fact_sheet_may_2013.pdf|archive-date=2015-05-04|url-status=dead}}</ref>。大型哺乳動物包括約十萬只鹿、近九萬只野豬、近五萬只狼和三萬多只狐狸，三分之一的築巢鳥類可以在里拉國家公園找到<ref name="EB Bio">{{cite encyclopedia|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Bulgaria#ref42692|title=Bulgaria: Plant and animal life|encyclopedia=Encyclopædia Britannica|first=John D.|last=Bell|access-date=2018-07-28|archive-date=2019-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191216150450/https://www.britannica.com/place/Bulgaria#ref42692}}</ref>，植物群包括 3,800 多種維管植物，其中170種是地方性的，150種被認為是瀕危的<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mycotaxon.com/resources/checklists/denchev-v111-checklist.pdf|title=Checklist of the larger basidiomycetes ın Bulgaria|publisher=Institute of Botany, Bulgarian Academy of Sciences|first=Cvetomir|last=Denchev|access-date=2018-09-12|archive-date=2022-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121024051/http://mycotaxon.com/resources/checklists/denchev-v111-checklist.pdf}}</ref>。

== 军事與外交 ==
{{main|保加利亞軍事}}
保加利亚于1955年12月14日被批准加入[[联合国|联合国]]，成为联合国成员国<ref>{{Cite web |title=A/RES/995 (X) : UN Documents : Security Council Report |url=https://www.securitycouncilreport.org/un-documents/document/unmembers-ares995-x.php |website=www.securitycouncilreport.org |publication-date=1955-12-14 |access-date=2022-06-11}}</ref>。自1966年以來，保加利亚已三度成為安理會非常任理事國，最近一次是在2002年至2003年期間<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thegreenpapers.com/ww/UNSecurityCouncil.phtml|title=The United Nations Security Council|publisher=The Green Papers Worldwide|access-date=2011-12-04|archive-date=2017-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171108031920/http://www.thegreenpapers.com/ww/UNSecurityCouncil.phtml}}</ref>。它也是聯合國安全組織的創始國之一。1975年的歐洲合作（歐安組織）。自共產主義垮台以來，歐洲-大西洋一體化一直是優先事項，儘管共產主義領導層也希望在1987年之前退出華沙條約並加入歐洲共同體<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2008/08/15/bai-toshoviiat-blian-bylgariia-v-es-prez-039-87.55776 |script-title=bg:Бай Тошовият блян – България в ЕС през '87 |trans-title=Todor Zhivkov's dream – Bulgaria in the EC in '87 |publisher=Dnes.bg |date=2008-08-15 |language=bg |access-date=2011-12-20 |archive-date=2012-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126214023/http://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2008/08/15/bai-toshoviiat-blian-bylgariia-v-es-prez-039-87.55776 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |script-title=bg:"Дойче веле": Тодор Живков искал България да стане член на ЕС |trans-title="Deutsche Welle": Todor Zhivkov wanted Bulgaria to join the EC |url=https://www.vesti.bg/novini/prez-1988-g.-komunisticheskiiat-lider-veche-iskal-ne-prosto-reforma-na-socializma-a-smiana-na-sistemata-1230064 |newspaper=Vesti |date=2008-09-03 |language=bg |access-date=2018-07-28 |archive-date=2022-05-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512223029/https://www.vesti.bg/novini/prez-1988-g.-komunisticheskiiat-lider-veche-iskal-ne-prosto-reforma-na-socializma-a-smiana-na-sistemata-1230064 }}</ref>。保加利亞於2005年4月25日簽署了《歐盟加入條約》<ref name="ec">{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/enlargement/archives/enlargement_process/future_prospects/negotiations/eu10_bulgaria_romania/treaty_2005_en.htm|title=European Commission Enlargement Archives: Treaty of Accession of Bulgaria and Romania|publisher=European Commission|date=2005-04-25|access-date=2011-12-20|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219145342/http://ec.europa.eu/enlargement/archives/enlargement_process/future_prospects/negotiations/eu10_bulgaria_romania/treaty_2005_en.htm|archive-date=2011-02-19}}</ref>，並於2007年1月1日成為歐盟的正式成員<ref name="Ind">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/the-big-question-with-romania-and-bulgaria-joining-the-eu-how-much-bigger-can-it-get-430061.html|title=The Big Question: With Romania and Bulgaria joining the EU, how much bigger can it get?|newspaper=[[The_Independent|The Independent]]|first=Steven|last=Castle|date=2006-12-29|access-date=2018-09-14|archive-date=2019-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116202327/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/the-big-question-with-romania-and-bulgaria-joining-the-eu-how-much-bigger-can-it-get-430061.html}}</ref>。此外，它與羅馬尼亞和希臘有三方經濟和外交合作<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.mfa.gr/www.mfa.gr/en-US/Policy/Geographic+Regions/South-Eastern+Europe/Balkans/Bilateral+Relations/Bulgaria/|title=Bulgaria – relations|publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Greece|access-date=2012-03-31|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120205023232/http://www2.mfa.gr/www.mfa.gr/en-US/Policy/Geographic+Regions/South-Eastern+Europe/Balkans/Bilateral+Relations/Bulgaria/|archive-date=2012-02-05}}</ref>。

在[[阿富汗戰爭_(2001年－2021年)|阿富汗戰爭]]期間，保加利亞派遣了6架飛機和200名士兵<ref name="CENTCOM">{{cite web|url=http://www.centcom.mil/bulgaria/ |title=Bulgaria Factbook |publisher=United States Central Command |date=December 2011 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111018052026/http://www.centcom.mil/bulgaria/ |archive-date=2011-10-18 |access-date=2018-10-04}}</ref>。隨著2004年3月加入北約和2006年4月簽署美國-保加利亞國防合作協議，保加利亚國際軍事關係進一步擴大<ref name="nato">{{cite web|url=http://www.nato.int/docu/update/2004/03-march/e0329a.htm|title=NATO Update: Seven new members join NATO|publisher=NATO|date=2004-03-29|access-date=2011-12-20|archive-date=2014-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315110351/http://www.nato.int/docu/update/2004/03-march/e0329a.htm}}</ref>。美國開始和保加利亞軍隊合作使用聯合軍事訓練設施<ref name="State">{{cite web|url=https://2009-2017.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/3236.htm|title=Bulgaria Factbook|publisher=Bureau of European and Eurasian Affairs, U.S. Department of State|access-date=2011-12-04|archive-date=2022-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220318174110/https://2009-2017.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/3236.htm}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.setimes.com/cocoon/setimes/xhtml/en_GB/features/setimes/features/2006/04/28/feature-01|title=US, Bulgaria sign defence co-operation agreement |publisher=[[Southeast_European_Times|Southeast European Times]] |date=2006-04-28 |access-date=2011-12-20 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110125201923/http://setimes.com/cocoon/setimes/xhtml/en_GB/features/setimes/features/2006/04/28/feature-01 |archive-date=2011-01-25 }}</ref>。儘管保加利亞積極開展國際防務合作，但仍是全球最和平的國家之一，在國內和國際衝突方面與冰島並列第6位，在全球和平指數中平均排名第26位<ref name="GPI">{{cite web |title=Global Peace Index 2019 |publisher=[[Institute_for_Economics_and_Peace|Institute for Economics and Peace]] |pages=8, 41, 96 |url=http://visionofhumanity.org/app/uploads/2019/06/GPI-2019-web003.pdf |access-date=2019-12-16 |archive-date=2019-08-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827155045/http://visionofhumanity.org/app/uploads/2019/06/GPI-2019-web003.pdf |url-status=dead }}</ref>。

國防是由陸軍、海軍和空軍組成的全志願保加利亞武裝部隊的責任。陸軍由2個機械化旅和8個獨立團營組成；空軍在六個空軍基地擁有 106 架飛機和防空系統，海軍則擁有各種艦船、直升機和海防武器<ref name="AF plan">{{cite web|url=http://www.mod.bg/en/doc/misc/20110207_AFDP_ENG.pdf|title=Armed Forces Development Plan|publisher=Ministry of Defence of Bulgaria|date=2010|access-date=2012-03-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120628195116/http://www.mod.bg/en/doc/misc/20110207_AFDP_ENG.pdf|archive-date=2012-06-28|url-status=dead}}</ref>。現役部隊從1988年的152,000人減少到2017年的31,300人，另外還有3,000名預備役人員和16,000名準軍事人員<ref>{{cite book|editor1-first=James|editor1-last=Hackett|title=The Military Balance 2017|publisher=[[Routledge|Routledge]]|page=96|year=2017|isbn=978-1857439007}}</ref>。軍事庫存主要包括蘇聯設備、S-300防空系統和SS-21 聖甲蟲短程彈道導彈<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.defence24.com/bulgaria-will-modernize-its-army-fighters-infantry-fighting-vehicles|title=Bulgaria Will Modernize Its Army. "Fighters, infantry fighting vehicles"|publisher=Defence24|first=Jakub|last=Palowski|date=2015-10-06|access-date=2018-07-21|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512223117/https://defence24.com/bulgaria-will-modernize-its-army-fighters-infantry-fighting-vehicles}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://aviationweek.com/site-files/aviationweek.com/files/uploads/2015/07/asd_08_06_2015_dossier.pdf|title=S-300 Surface-to-air Missile System|publisher=Aerospace Daily & Defense Report|date=2015-08-06|access-date=2018-07-21|archive-date=2019-08-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190808002052/https://aviationweek.com/site-files/aviationweek.com/files/uploads/2015/07/asd_08_06_2015_dossier.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://nationalinterest.org/blog/ss-21-scarab-russias-forgotten-deadly-ballistic-missile-17679?page=0%2C1|title=SS-21 Scarab: Russia's Forgotten (But Deadly) Ballistic Missile|magazine=The National Interest|first=Sebastien|last=Roblin|date=2016-09-12|access-date=2018-07-21|archive-date=2022-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220512223126/https://nationalinterest.org/blog/ss-21-scarab-russias-forgotten-deadly-ballistic-missile-17679?page=0%2C1}}</ref>。
